Pancreatitis as a complication of endovascular aneurysm repair. We report a case of acute pancreatitis complicating an endovascular abdominal aortic aneurysm repair (EVAR).A seventy three year old man underwent an EVAR and developed acute onset epigastric pain, followed by mottling of the upper abdominal wall. A raised amylase confirmed the diagnosis of acute pancreatitis.To our knowledge this is the first report of this complication of EVAR.